Honey Garlic Ground Beef
  --Patty Catalano

1/3 c water
1/3 c honey
1 tbsp cornstarch
3 tbsp shoyu or tamari
1/4 tsp red pepper flakes (optional)
1 tbsp neutral oil, such as canola or avocado
1 pound lean ground beef
4 cloves garlic, minced
Rice, toasted sesame seeds, and sliced scallions for serving

Whisk water, honey, cornstarch, shoyu, and red pepper flakes if using together in a small bowl. Heat 1 tablespoon neutral oil in a large 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat until shimmering. Add ground beef and garlic and cook, breaking up the meat into small pieces, until cooked through and browned, 6-8 min. Stir the sauce again, then pour into the skillet. Cook, stirring often, until the sauce is thickened, glossy, and coats the beef, 2-3 min. Serve with cooked white rice and garnish with toasted sesame seeds and thinly sliced scallions if using.

